The `getRepository()` function is a utility method designed to retrieve the current repository instance within the code. It attempts to return `base.cr`, which is a common way to access the repository in many applications. If this fails, it falls back to returning `simbase.air`. This function is part of a suite of utility functions made available as built-ins, allowing developers to easily access key components of the system without needing direct references to them.

def getRepository():
    try:
        return base.cr
    except Exception:
        return simbase.air
